            "comments": [
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Jeffery",
                        "email": "andrew@codeconstruct.com.au",
                        "username": "amboar"
                    },
                    "message": "Hi Kyle, this document desperately needs content in the `Alternatives Considered` section. The design document template explicitly states[1] that proposals should be written as argumentative essays[2] that compel the readers to agree with your conclusion. I do not find the argument so far to be compelling given the existence of the C++ bindings provided by libgpiod:\n\nhttps://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/libs/libgpiod/libgpiod.git/tree/bindings/cxx?h=v2.1\n\nIf necessary, please revise the document to argue your case in the face of what's already provided by libgpiod.\n\n[1]: https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/master/designs/design-template.md?plain=1#L16-L19\n[2]: https://www.grammarly.com/blog/argumentative-essay/"
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/gpio-monitor-lib.md",
                    "line": 74,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Jeffery",
                        "email": "andrew@codeconstruct.com.au",
                        "username": "amboar"
                    },
                    "message": "Please argue why the C++ binding provided by libgpiod doesn't fit your requirements.\n\nhttps://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/libs/libgpiod/libgpiod.git/tree/bindings/cxx?h=v2.1"
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/gpio-monitor-lib.md",
                    "line": 87,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "I'm having trouble determining what the scope/structure of this \"library\" looks like.  We generally don't want to have shared libraries.  If this is valuable to have as a shared library, I'd be curious why it shouldn't go into the C++ bindings of libgpiod.\n\nIf all that is being proposed is a refactor of phosphor-gpio-monitor for consistency, go for it.  We don't necessarily need a project-wide design doc for that.\n\nIf you really do want a new shared library, I think this document needs a lot more content/context as to what the shared library will provide and what the API will look like.  (And we would need the alternatives considered filled out with why libgpiod enhancements are off the table.)"
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/gpio-monitor-lib.md",
                    "line": 87,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Kyle Nieman",
                        "email": "kyle.nieman@fii-na.com",
                        "username": "Kyle-Nieman"
                    },
                    "message": "Thank you for the feedback. I will update the proposal accordingly."
                }
